SIMPLE: attributive
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Attributive
<hw>At*trib"u*tive</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>attributif</ets>.]</ety> <def>Attributing; pertaining to,
expressing, or assigning an attribute; of the nature of an
attribute.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Attributive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Attributive
<hw>At*trib"u*tive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>, <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>A word
that denotes an attribute; esp. a modifying word joined to a noun; an
adjective or adjective phrase.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Attributively</ent>⟦br⟧
